Florence s Cathedral the Duomo ItalyFlorence s cathedral stands tall over the city with its magnificent Renaissance dome designed by Filippo Brunelleschi with the baptistery right across The cathedral named in honor of Santa Maria del Fiore is a vast Gothic structure built on the site of the th century church of Santa Reparata the remains of which can be seen in the crypt The cathedral was begun at the end of the th century by Arnolfo di Cambio and the dome which dominates the exterior was added in the th century on a design of Filippo Brunelleschi A statue to each of these important architects can be found outside to the right of the cathedral both admiring their work for the rest of eternity Can you imagine it took two centuries for the cathedral to be deemed finished The dome of Florence Cathedral is the largest masonry dome in the world and was constructed using over million bricks and weighs tons Source churches duomo html travel photography gram
